        <body>

            <pb n="1"/>

            <p>With the Help of the Almighty God.</p>
            <p><placeName>Philadelphia</placeName> Thursday.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Chapter of the week&#58; &#8220;You shall command&#8221;<lb/> of the
                year <date>5618</date>.</p>
            <p>Greetings to the highly esteemed father<lb/> the famous scholar Rabbi
                        <sic><addressee>Isaac Lesser</addressee></sic><lb/> in peace &#38; freedom
                will follow surround you till<lb/> the moon will stop to exist
                <sic>exist</sic>.<lb/>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">My dear beloved sir&#58;</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Last week I was informed&#44;<lb/> that the directors of the Holy
                Community<lb/> Bnai&#8211;Israel intend to elect you&#44; my friend&#44;<lb/> as a
                judge and preside&#44; when the cantor<lb/> will read the
                    <add>&#91;Hebrew&#93;</add> megilah.</p>

            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>according to the custom of the sons of Israel<lb/> Last Monday was<hi rend="sup"
                    >2</hi> held a meeting<hi rend="sup">1</hi> and the directors<lb/> decided&#44;
                that your Honor shall be one of the judges<lb/> during the time&#44; when the
                megilah <add>&#91;Hebrew&#93;</add><lb/> will be read on all also to every coming
                year Kal&#8211;Midrai <add>&#91;Hebrew&#93;</add><lb/> The directors gave me the
                    <add>Hebrew</add> the liberty to send<lb/> you a letter in appreciation and
                respect due<lb/> to your personality and the letter was sent to <persName>Mr<lb/> Mr.
                    S. Blitz&#44;</persName> who refused to forward to you&#44; as<lb/> he
                noticed in the letter many mistakes&#44; and<lb/> especially&#44; when the members
                of the community read<lb/> it when they had their meeting on Saturday&#44; and
                it<lb/> they decided&#44; that such a letter is below the dignity<lb/> &#40;or
                    furtige<add>&#63;</add>&#41; of the community&#44; so they applied</p>

            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>to me to notify you about and I have my full confidence<lb/> in them and in their
                sayings. I also <sic>inclosed</sic> the<lb/> mentioned above letter in this letter
                and your<lb/> honor shall forgive and return the letter c&#47;o<lb/> the eve. the
                idea is that this incident<lb/> shall remain in strict confidence and shall<lb/> not
                reach any publicity. I hope that you under&#8211;<lb/> stand the hint I hope that
                the hing is under&#8211;<lb/>stood. And shall your Honor be informed<lb/> that with
                the coming fast of Esther we&#39;ll shout<lb/> our <add>Hebrew</add> prayers at 5
                p.m.<lb/> and shall the lord prolong his your life<lb/> that you&#39;ll be able to
                see all the<lb/> wonders&#44; that as God did so our ancestors</p>

            <pb n="4"/>
            <p>in the ancient times.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">From me the writer who</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">loves you and remain your</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">obedient servant.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><add>&#91;Hebrew&#93;</add>
                <persName role="author">Simon Picnot</persName>.</p>


